The paper proposes a method for temporal action localization using a combination of spatial and temporal CNNs. This is a computer vision task, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also mentions end-to-end training and optimization, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper uses a public dataset for evaluation, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning and neural networks, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper involves the task of action recognition, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
